n245:   - Verify 401 returned\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-033**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_ExpiredToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n248:   - Request with expired token\n249:   - Verify 401 returned\n250: \n251: - [ ] **TEST-034**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_SkipPath` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n252:   - Request to /health (skipped path)\n253:   - Verify auth not required\n254:   - Verify next handler called\n255: \n256: - [ ] **TEST-035**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_InvalidAuthHeader` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n257:   - Request with non-Bearer auth scheme\n258:   - Verify 401 returned\n259: \n260: - [ ] **TEST-036**: Create `TestExtractToken` in `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`\n261:   - Valid Bearer header → token extracted\n262:   - Missing header → error\n263:   - Malformed header → error\n264: \n265: #### Config Tests\n266: \n267: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `TestLoadConfig_AuthConfig` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n268:   - Load auth config from environment\n269:   - Verify defaults applied\n270: \n271: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Create `TestConfig_Validate_AuthMode` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n272:   - AuthMode=picod without key → error\n273:   - AuthMode=picod with key → valid\n274:   - AuthMode=none → valid\n275: \n276: ### Phase 9: Integration Tests\n277: \n278: - [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_FullFlow` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n279:   - Start real HTTP server with JWT middleware\n280:   - Make request with valid token\n281:   - Verify 200 OK\n282:   - Make request without token\n283:   - Verify 401 Unauthorized\n284: \n285: - [ ] **TEST-051**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_MultipleRequests` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n286:   - Concurrent requests with valid tokens\n287:   - Verify all succeed\n288:   - Verify no race conditions (run with -race)\n289: \n290: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_HealthEndpoint` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n291:   - Health endpoint without token → 200 OK\n292:   - Protected endpoint without token → 401\n293:   - Verify skip paths work in real server\n294: \n295: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Create `TestJWTMiddleware_Integration_TokenTampering` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n296:   - Modify valid token payload\n297:   - Verify signature check fails\n298:   - Verify 401 returned\n299: \n300: - [ ] **TEST-054**: Create `TestSetupHTTPServer_Integration` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n301:   - Full server setup with auth enabled\n302:   - Verify middleware applied\n303:   - Verify server responds correctly\n304: \n305: ### Phase 10: Documentation\n306: \n307: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types in `crypto.go`, `jwt.go`, `errors.go`, `middleware.go`\n308:   - Include parameter descriptions\n309:   - Include return value descriptions\n310:   - Include error conditions\n311: \n312: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add usage examples in doc comments\n313:   - Example: creating JWT middleware\n314:   - Example: loading public key\n315:   - Example: validating token\n316: \n317: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/picod/README.md`\n318:   - Document JWT authentication\n319:   - Include configuration options\n320:   - Include token format requirements\n321:   - Include error handling guide\n322: \n323: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add security documentation\n324:   - RSA key management best practices\n325:   - Token lifetime recommendations\n326:   - Clock skew considerations\n327:   - Key rotation strategy\n328: \n329: ## Acceptance Criteria\n330: \n331: - [ ] JWT middleware correctly validates tokens with RSA signatures\n332: - [ ] Invalid/missing tokens return 401 Unauthorized\n333: - [ ] Expired tokens are rejected\n334: - [ ] Signature verification works with RSA public key (PKIX and PKCS#1 formats)\n335: - [ ] Configurable skip paths work correctly\n336: - [ ] Health endpoint can be protected or public\n337: - [ ] Claims are correctly parsed and validated (exp, iat, sub, iss, aud)\n338: - [ ] Clock skew tolerance is configurable\n339: - [ ] Error types map to appropriate HTTP status codes\n340: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n341: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n342: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n343: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n344: - [ ] Compatible with standard JWT libraries (PyJWT, node-jose, etc.)\n345: - [ ] RS256 (RSA-PKCS1v15 with SHA256) signature algorithm implemented\n346: \n347: ## Dependencies\n348: \n349: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n350: |------------|--------|-------|\n351: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA signature verification |\n352: | `crypto/x509` | Standard | X.509 key parsing |\n353: | `crypto/rand` | Standard | Key generation |\n354: | `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM decoding |\n355: | `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding |\n356: | `encoding/json` | Standard | JSON claims parsing |\n357: | `net/http` | Standard | HTTP middleware |\n358: | `strings` | Standard | String manipulation |\n359: | `time` | Standard | Token time validation |\n360: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Structured logging |\n361: | AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n362: | AR-016 (PicoD File Management API) | Completed | Base infrastructure |\n363: \n364: ## Implementation Order\n365: \n366: ```\n367: TASK-001 → TASK-005 (Crypto utilities)\n368:     ↓\n369: TASK-010 → TASK-013 (JWT claims & validation)\n370:     ↓\n371: TASK-020 → TASK-023 (Auth errors)\n372:     ↓\n373: TASK-030 → TASK-034 (HTTP middleware)\n374:     ↓\n375: TASK-040 → TASK-042 (Response helpers)\n376:     ↓\n377: TASK-050 → TASK-053 (Configuration)\n378:     ↓\n379: TASK-060 → TASK-063 (PicoD integration)\n380:     ↓\n381: TEST-001 → TEST-041 (Unit tests)\n382:     ↓\n383: TEST-050 → TEST-054 (Integration tests)\n384:     ↓\n385: DOC-001 → DOC-004 (Documentation)\n386: ```\n387: \n388: ## Test Infrastructure\n389: \n390: - [ ] **TEST-060**: Create `generateTestToken(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, claims *Claims) (string, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n391:   - Create JWT header (RS256)\n392:   - Encode claims as JSON\n393:   - Sign with private key\n394:   - Return complete token\n395: \n396: - [ ] **TEST-061**: Create `testClaims() *Claims` helper in `pkg/picod/jwt_test.go`\n397:   - Return standard test claims with valid timestamps\n398: \n399: - [ ] **TEST-062**: Create `generateTestKeyPair() (*rsa.PrivateKey, *rsa.PublicKey, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/crypto_test.go`\n400:   - Generate RSA key pair for tests\n401:   - Use smaller key size (1024 bits) for speed\n402: \n403: - [ ] **TEST-063**: Create `newTestServer(handler http.Handler) (*httptest.Server, error)` helper in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n404:   - Create test HTTP server\n405:   - Return server and cleanup function\n406: \n407: ## Coverage Verification\n408: \n409: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n410:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n411:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n412:   - Verify crypto.go, jwt.go, errors.go, middleware.go all covered\n413:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n414: \n415: ## Security Considerations\n416: \n417: - [ ] **SEC-001**: Verify RSA signature uses SHA256 (RS256)\n418: - [ ] **SEC-002**: Verify clock skew prevents replay attacks\n419: - [ ] **SEC-003**: Verify token parsing rejects malformed input\n420: - [ ] **SEC-004**: Verify key loading rejects invalid formats\n421: - [ ] **SEC-005**: Verify error messages don't leak sensitive info\n\n(End of file - total 421 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT Middleware Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: RSA Key Handling (`crypto.go`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/picod/crypto.go`\n  - Define package-level imports: `crypto/rsa`, `crypto/x509`, `encoding/pem`, `encoding/base64`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `LoadPublicKey(pemData []byte) (*rsa.PublicKey, error)` in `pkg/picod/crypto.go`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775862457655,"end":1775862457686}}}}
